{"word":"ἐπεύνακτοι","slug":"ἐπεύνακτοι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n38780\" key=\"e)peu/naktoi\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἐπεύνακτοι</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ων</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">οἱ</gen>, (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">εὐνάζω</etym>) name for the Helots who were adopted into their lords' places during the Messenian wars, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0566.tlg001:166\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Theopomp.Hist.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">166</biblScope> </bibl>:—<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0060.tlg001.perseus-grc3:8\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.S.\">D.S.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8</biblScope> </bibl> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fr.\">Fr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">21</biblScope> </bibl> writes <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἐπευνακταί</orth>, and seems to identify them with the <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">παρθενίαι</foreign> (q. v.): <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl> has <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐνεύνακτοι· οἱ παρθενίαι,</foreign> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐπευνακταί· οἱ συγκοιμηταί.</foreign> </entryFree>"}]}